<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The current Zend_View_Helper_Url allows an associative array to pass values and assemble a URL. It would be great if the helper could not only support:-</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
echo $this-&gt;url(array('controller' =&gt; 'home', 'action' =&gt; 'news', 'module' =&gt; 'default', 'id' =&gt; 3), 'default', true)
</code></pre>

<p>but also numeric indices to provide parameters in the same way that the Zend_Controller methods accept URLs in the 'action, controller, module, params' strategy. E.g.</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
echo $this-&gt;url(array('news', 'home', 'default', array('id' =&gt; 3)), 'default', true)
</code></pre>

<p>This usage would be BC and non-intrusive, but allow slightly less verbose view code.</p>

    </div>
